<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Template for Secrets.plist.

  Secrets.plist is gitignored so real keys never reach GitHub. To set up:
    1. Copy this file to "Secrets.plist" in the same folder.
    2. Replace the placeholder below with your Congress.gov API key
       (get one free at https://api.congress.gov/sign-up/).

  Until a real key is present, the app falls back to bundled sample data.

  Key pools: each key below may be either a single <string> or an <array>
  of <string>s. When you supply an array, every install is randomly assigned
  one key from the pool (the choice is remembered per install), spreading load
  so no single key hits its rate limit. Add more keys to the array anytime —
  no code change is needed. Example:

      <key>CongressGovAPIKey</key>
      <array>
          <string>FIRST_CONGRESS_GOV_API_KEY</string>
          <string>SECOND_CONGRESS_GOV_API_KEY</string>
      </array>

  OpenFECAPIKey is optional. It powers the profile's "Top Funders" section
  with real campaign-finance data from OpenFEC (get a free key at
  https://api.data.gov/signup/). Without it, that section simply stays empty.

  CensusAPIKey is optional. It powers the district/state map sheets'
  population, demographics, and top-industries sections with real Census ACS
  data (get a free key instantly at
  https://api.census.gov/data/key_signup.html). Note this is a Census-issued
  key, NOT the same as an api.data.gov key. Without it, those sections stay
  empty; the keyless top-cities and top-universities lookups still work.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>CongressGovAPIKey</key>
	<array>
		<string>YOUR_CONGRESS_GOV_API_KEY</string>
	</array>
	<key>OpenFECAPIKey</key>
	<string>YOUR_OPENFEC_API_KEY</string>
	<key>CensusAPIKey</key>
	<array>
		<string>YOUR_CENSUS_API_KEY</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
